liblazy
------------------------------------------
Liblazy is a simple and easy to use library that provides convenient functions
for sending messages over the D-Bus daemon, querying information from HAL or
asking PolicyKit for a privilege.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.15-1
  libdbus1_3-1.4.20-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-10-1
  automake-4-10
  binutils-2.22.51-2
  cygport-0.10.10-1
  gawk-4.0.1-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/liblazy

Canonical download:
  git://anongit.freedesktop.org/liblazy

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack liblazy-0.2+git20071107-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./liblazy-0.2+git20071107-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/liblazy-0.2+git20071107-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/liblazy-0.2+git20071107-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/liblazy1-0.2+git20071107-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/liblazy-devel-0.2+git20071107-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(liblazy)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/liblazy.README
  /usr/share/doc/liblazy/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/liblazy/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/liblazy/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/liblazy/README

(liblazy1)
  /usr/bin/cyglazy-1.dll

(liblazy-devel)
  /usr/include/liblazy.h
  /usr/lib/liblazy.dll.a
  /usr/lib/liblazy.la
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/lazy.pc

